                  </persName>
             sworn. - I work for Mr. Murdon; I drive a cart and two horses: Last Monday, between two and three o'clock, I was going to Brick-lane, I stopped the cart to see if my load was ready; I had fastened my coat to the spindle of the copses of the cart; the prisoner gave it a hitch, and then went on; then he turned back and gave it the other hitch; then I saw him take the coat, and put it in a sack that he had.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I found it.</p>
